---
title: One-Pot Chicken Sausage & Chickpea Soup with Spinach & Italian Seasoning
description: No matter the weather, it’s normal to crave a big bowl of soup (i.e. the culinary equivalent of a bear hug). Enter this hearty, soul-warming rendition. It’s chock-full of goodness—that is to say spiced chicken sausage, tender chickpeas, wilted spinach, and a bevy of Italian herbs in a rich, tomatoey broth. Soup’s on!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/6226135c8a554c23fb7d9d6a-fcdaf3b0.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/one-pot-chicken-sausage-chickpea-soup-6226135c8a554c23fb7d9d6a-cf591183.pdf
author: Michelle Doll Olson
course: main course
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/one-pot-chicken-sausage-and-chickpea-soup-6226135c8a554c23fb7d9d6a
time required: 25 minutes
cuisine: Italian
nutrition:
  calories: 600 kcal
  fat: 21 g
  saturated fat: 4.5 g
  carbohydrates: 56 g
  sugar: 12 g
  protein: 38 g
  fiber: 9 g
  sodium: 2080 mg
---

Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and finely dice @yellow onion{1}. Drain and rinse @chickpeas{13.4%ounce}.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon} in a large #pot{} over medium-high heat. Add @Italian chicken sausage mix{9%ounce} and cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Add onion; cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Stir in @tomato paste{1.5%ounce} and half the @Italian seasoning{1%tablespoon} (all for 4 servings); cook, stirring, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir 2 1/2 cups water (5 cups for 4 servings), @chicken stock concentrate{2}, chickpeas, and a big pinch of @salt into pot. Cover and bring to a boil, then reduce heat to medium. Simmer, covered, ~{7%minutes}.

Once soup has simmered, uncover pot and stir in @baby spinach{5%ounce}. Simmer until spinach has wilted, ~{2-3%minutes} more. Season generously with @salt and @pepper to taste.

Divide soup between #bowls{} and serve.